1
00:00:01,060 --> 00:00:18,327
Namo Tassa Bhagavato Arahato Sambha Sambhodasa Namo Tassa Bhagavato Arahato Sambha Sambhodasa

2
00:00:18,695 --> 00:00:25,403
Namo tassa bhagavato arahato samma sambuddhasa.

3
00:00:26,044 --> 00:00:32,872
Homage to the Buddha, the blessed, noble, and fully self-awakened one.

4
00:00:32,893 --> 00:00:35,256
Okay, so we're celebrating the moon night.

5
00:00:35,476 --> 00:00:45,850
Actually, I think it's on Wednesday, but we have to bend the rules a bit for our culture, so we're doing it tonight.

6
00:00:46,942 --> 00:00:49,847
And the topic is on karma and rebirth.

7
00:00:50,770 --> 00:00:58,122
So just going through the sort of basics, really, just being sure as to what we mean by personal karma.

8
00:00:59,005 --> 00:01:01,490
In other words, the karma that leads to liberation.

9
00:01:03,133 --> 00:01:11,027
So we understand in Buddhism that there are five laws, the first one being karma.

10
00:01:11,597 --> 00:01:12,739
called the law of heat.

11
00:01:12,819 --> 00:01:13,980
That's how it translates.

12
00:01:15,683 --> 00:01:19,868
But it's really to do with what we would call physics and chemistry, just matter.

13
00:01:20,709 --> 00:01:27,399
So those are laws which are separate from personal responsibility.

14
00:01:27,778 --> 00:01:33,066
Now, what I think is really pointing to here is things like the tsunami.

15
00:01:33,248 --> 00:01:44,179
So in the East, if you were a victim of the tsunami, they would tend to think that was because in some past life, you must have drowned somebody or something worse.

16
00:01:44,578 --> 00:01:47,281
So it gets a bit far-fetched.

17
00:01:47,581 --> 00:01:56,230
So we have to be clear that the Earth matter has its own properties, and we happen to be born at this time.

18
00:01:56,811 --> 00:02:01,956
Now, there is this connection, of course, with climate change, but that comes later.

19
00:02:04,281 --> 00:02:06,965
The next one is hereditary.

20
00:02:08,046 --> 00:02:08,507
Excuse me.

21
00:02:08,546 --> 00:02:22,223
You can't, you know, if you're born with a disease coming from your parents and their parents and back all the way, that's not your personal karma.

22
00:02:23,025 --> 00:02:28,331
That's to do with, you know, being born with that certain genetic makeup.

23
00:02:29,358 --> 00:02:32,481
Now, what is your personal karma is how you relate to it.

24
00:02:32,762 --> 00:02:34,985
And again, we'll come to that in a minute.

25
00:02:35,764 --> 00:02:53,385
So it's to think of somebody who is born, say, with Down syndrome and to think that they are therefore must have been some sort of animal in the past life and that they're born at the same level of intelligence.

26
00:02:53,866 --> 00:02:54,807
That wouldn't be correct.

27
00:02:55,068 --> 00:02:58,572
OK, even they have their own karma to work out.

28
00:03:00,694 --> 00:03:03,337
The next one would be citta.

29
00:03:03,957 --> 00:03:06,100
So this is our psychology.

30
00:03:06,561 --> 00:03:09,824
So we're born with a certain set of psychological rules.

31
00:03:10,245 --> 00:03:11,425
And that's as simple as that.

32
00:03:11,747 --> 00:03:14,830
A simple one would be just the way we learn language.

33
00:03:14,849 --> 00:03:18,973
And that's all to do with the mind, the wake up of the mind and the brain.

34
00:03:18,993 --> 00:03:28,204
So remember, in the Buddha's teaching, the mind and the body are two separate energy systems.

35
00:03:28,183 --> 00:03:33,812
And when we're reborn, it's the mind that leaves the body.

36
00:03:34,674 --> 00:03:40,402
And we'll come to that again when we have just a quick reminder of what rebirth is.

37
00:03:40,423 --> 00:03:48,574
So again, you have to be very careful when we're talking about personal karma, the karma that leads to liberation or not.

38
00:03:48,594 --> 00:03:50,377
It's the opposite way too.

39
00:03:50,526 --> 00:03:54,212
And this leads us to the problem of social karma.

40
00:03:54,272 --> 00:04:03,669
So a lot of people might talk about social karma, meaning the karma of, say, being born in British culture or in another culture.

41
00:04:04,430 --> 00:04:09,117
And again, that wouldn't be quite the way that the Buddha would see it.

42
00:04:09,198 --> 00:04:12,484
He would see it more as a collection of individuals.

43
00:04:12,463 --> 00:04:19,336
And the collection of individuals have agreed to certain rules and regulations, certain cultural norms.

44
00:04:19,817 --> 00:04:24,125
Most of this is passed on to us, whether we like it or not, when we're children.

45
00:04:25,228 --> 00:04:34,505
But it's not as though it's something that is out there as a social or as something separate from individuals.

46
00:04:34,790 --> 00:04:35,130
Right.

47
00:04:35,672 --> 00:04:46,372
The whatever is passed on to us through our societies is passed on individually through our parents, through through the media and so on and so forth.

48
00:04:46,392 --> 00:04:49,319
So, again, it's about individuals.

49
00:04:50,139 --> 00:04:51,583
And it's the same when we.

50
00:04:53,048 --> 00:05:07,189
You know, when you think about, say, thousands of deaths from famine or thousands of deaths from all these conflicts that are going on, all that really is individuals who are dying.

51
00:05:07,930 --> 00:05:09,572
And some will die very peacefully.

52
00:05:09,692 --> 00:05:11,415
Some will not have suffered greatly.

53
00:05:11,755 --> 00:05:13,778
And others, of course, will have died in agony.

54
00:05:14,620 --> 00:05:17,605
But again, it's all very individual.

55
00:05:18,266 --> 00:05:22,531
It's our universe, right?

56
00:05:22,781 --> 00:05:36,141
So if you think about it, everything that we're experiencing is coming in through the senses and through our own particular conditioning.

57
00:05:37,223 --> 00:05:41,831
And what we're experiencing now is our own little universe.

58
00:05:42,230 --> 00:05:44,014
And we're always at the center of it.

59
00:05:44,973 --> 00:05:53,915
So when somebody steps into that universe and does us harm, that isn't our personal karma.

60
00:05:53,935 --> 00:05:57,483
That's coming from their decision-making.

61
00:05:58,225 --> 00:06:00,552
Our personal karma is how we react to

62
00:06:02,067 --> 00:06:10,406
So that takes us into the next section about karma itself, the law of karma.

63
00:06:10,425 --> 00:06:11,889
And this is all about ethics.

64
00:06:12,089 --> 00:06:19,687
And you could say that the Buddha really, you know, you could reduce all his teachings to ethics and transcendence.

65
00:06:20,444 --> 00:06:30,264
And the reason for that, remember, is that because of this delusion that we are suffering from, we enter into a wrong relationship.

66
00:06:30,283 --> 00:06:40,444
So when we look at our ethical, moral behavior, that will be a measure of our wisdom or lack of it.

67
00:06:42,161 --> 00:06:48,709
So there's a connection there between the process of liberation and ethics.

68
00:06:49,310 --> 00:06:55,237
So there's always this purification has to go on at the same time as insight.

69
00:06:56,358 --> 00:07:07,851
You can't have insight and still go around, you know, murdering people and robbing from them and getting wild on drugs.

70
00:07:07,911 --> 00:07:08,331
You can't.

71
00:07:08,452 --> 00:07:09,673
It's not possible.

72
00:07:09,913 --> 00:07:10,514
Right.

73
00:07:10,951 --> 00:07:25,973
because of the connection between the delusion and how it manifests and the process of beginning to undermine that delusion through the process of ethical behavior.

74
00:07:25,952 --> 00:07:32,045
And that's all put out, of course, in the eightfold path, you know, right speech, right action, right livelihood.

75
00:07:32,625 --> 00:07:41,584
And the more we work on that, the more it sort of feeds back into the way that we understand the world.

76
00:07:44,970 --> 00:07:47,454
So that karma...

77
00:07:47,940 --> 00:07:52,423
When we talk about the law of karma, we're talking really about ethics.

78
00:07:52,442 --> 00:07:56,904
And that's now beginning to be where our...

79
00:07:57,982 --> 00:08:00,985
Well, the core work is, you might say.

80
00:08:01,846 --> 00:08:04,367
The final one is to do with Dharma.

81
00:08:04,949 --> 00:08:17,620
And these are, of course, the basic teachings of the Buddha, the Four Noble Truths, the Law of Karma itself, and Wheel of Dependent Origination, Dependent Origination itself too.

82
00:08:18,180 --> 00:08:22,946
So all that teaching of the Buddha comes under the Law of the Dharma.

83
00:08:23,365 --> 00:08:27,550
The Dharma itself is the truth that will...

84
00:08:27,529 --> 00:08:32,557
when we take it on, will lead us to the end of our own personal inner suffering.

85
00:08:32,938 --> 00:08:40,090
OK, so remember, the suffering we're talking about is to do with wrong understanding.

86
00:08:40,230 --> 00:08:43,154
So it doesn't include physical suffering.

87
00:08:43,535 --> 00:08:47,282
You know, so long as we have a body, it's going to give us pain.

88
00:08:47,381 --> 00:08:49,926
It's just it's just the way it is.

89
00:08:49,905 --> 00:09:10,544
But the heart, once cleansed of all its negativity, of all its unwholesome habits and understandings, begins to be in a state of one of the four great illimitables, one of the four Brahma Viharas.

90
00:09:10,946 --> 00:09:18,832
It's in some state of love or some state of compassion, some state of joy or just peaceful equanimity.

91
00:09:19,453 --> 00:09:22,677
So, you know, that's the Buddha heart, yeah?

92
00:09:23,298 --> 00:09:30,907
But don't confuse that with the Buddha itself, with the Buddha within, which is this pure awareness.

93
00:09:31,808 --> 00:09:37,575
Remember, the awareness is within this psychophysical organism, right?

94
00:09:37,595 --> 00:09:44,823
And it's through this organism that it's manifesting its delusion or its wisdom, yeah?

95
00:09:47,047 --> 00:09:47,486
Okay.

96
00:09:48,985 --> 00:09:49,947
So that's the Dharma.

97
00:09:50,587 --> 00:10:08,256
So the point here is to be very clear as to what is our personal karma, the karma that leads to either continued rebirth or to liberation.

98
00:10:09,399 --> 00:10:14,908
And it all comes back to the dependence origination and to the point of

99
00:10:15,985 --> 00:10:18,869
reaction to what we're experiencing.

100
00:10:19,448 --> 00:10:19,610
Right.

101
00:10:20,390 --> 00:10:21,852
And that's all just a minute.

102
00:10:22,153 --> 00:10:23,014
I don't know what this is.

103
00:10:24,556 --> 00:10:25,277
Thank you very much.

104
00:10:25,616 --> 00:10:32,306
That's a bit of an interruption from from Dell.

105
00:10:32,326 --> 00:10:32,866
Can't help it.

106
00:10:32,907 --> 00:10:35,529
You know, it's just one of those things.

107
00:10:36,522 --> 00:11:03,356
So dependent origination, what it's saying is that this tanha, this wrong relationship to things that we call attachment, indulgence, aversion, fear, all these sorts of reactions to what we are experiencing is the cause of our unsatisfactoriness, our suffering and our continued suffering.

108
00:11:03,471 --> 00:11:12,341
And it's when we undermine that, that we begin to roll that wheel backwards upon itself.

109
00:11:12,863 --> 00:11:19,690
And we come down to the root problem, which is about our sense of identity.

110
00:11:20,571 --> 00:11:22,153
That's where the root is.

111
00:11:22,474 --> 00:11:27,318
Remember, his victory verse is that he had discovered the house builder.

112
00:11:27,788 --> 00:11:33,918
And he's broken down, he's found the house builder, he's broken the house, he's broken this and he's broken that.

113
00:11:34,378 --> 00:11:35,419
It all sounds very violent.

114
00:11:35,941 --> 00:11:38,203
And he's liberated himself.

115
00:11:38,264 --> 00:11:46,977
He's found the citta, that knowing which is the Buddha within.

116
00:11:46,957 --> 00:11:52,044
So that's the root problem as to what we identify with.

117
00:11:52,205 --> 00:12:01,538
And remember that when you are practicing vipassana, you've pulled yourself out of this organism into this observer, right?

118
00:12:02,078 --> 00:12:06,905
And that observer really recognizes it as a place of untouchability.

119
00:12:07,225 --> 00:12:10,410
Once you're established there, nothing can harm you.

120
00:12:11,030 --> 00:12:16,458
Really sort of grasp that because that's very close to our liberation, yeah?

121
00:12:18,379 --> 00:12:23,506
So when it comes to something like rebirth, it's not within our culture.

122
00:12:23,528 --> 00:12:26,171
It's a bit difficult for us to sort of get our head around that.

123
00:12:28,053 --> 00:12:35,043
The fact that we might be reborn into another place, another time, take on a different personality.

124
00:12:36,046 --> 00:12:47,221
And yet through that personality, whatever unwholesomeness and wholesomeness we have in terms of the way we look at things will again begin to manifest.

125
00:12:47,894 --> 00:13:02,562
So really, for those that find it just difficult to, you know, to, to accept, it's a case of just putting it on the back burner, you know, I mean, there'll come a point when we'll know for sure, right?

126
00:13:03,654 --> 00:13:05,797
And that's when we leave the planet.

127
00:13:06,498 --> 00:13:09,500
So there's no point in rushing the decision.

128
00:13:09,860 --> 00:13:12,903
The decision will be made for us when we die.

129
00:13:13,384 --> 00:13:18,428
And if after all, it's just annihilation, we just disappear.

130
00:13:18,889 --> 00:13:20,812
Well, there's no problem in that at all, is there?

131
00:13:20,831 --> 00:13:23,673
I mean, there's no suffering involved in that whatsoever.

132
00:13:24,654 --> 00:13:29,279
So it's best not to come to a decision about that.

133
00:13:29,600 --> 00:13:32,682
There's no need, for instance, to come to a conclusion.

134
00:13:32,663 --> 00:13:42,573
If we don't have that information, and we're talking about information which is experiential, this is not science.

135
00:13:43,333 --> 00:13:46,577
We're never going to prove it with a thermometer or something.

136
00:13:47,077 --> 00:13:54,687
It's just something which is beyond our ability to know in that sort of way.

137
00:13:56,427 --> 00:13:59,851
But there are people who have...

138
00:14:00,423 --> 00:14:06,369
come out of the body and have gone to such places, and they stand as witness to that possibility.

139
00:14:06,690 --> 00:14:11,715
So really, it's just a case of keeping it as a possibility.

140
00:14:12,115 --> 00:14:23,528
I mean, in the fullness of the teaching, it gives you some idea of the grand moral value

141
00:14:24,706 --> 00:14:32,322
laws that go right through the cosmos, through all the different levels of being.

142
00:14:32,884 --> 00:14:42,866
There is this law of karma, which is basically saying, if you're coming from a wrong place, you're going to end up unhappy.

143
00:14:42,846 --> 00:14:49,697
If you're coming from a deluded place, you're going to keep finding yourself in an unhappy situation.

144
00:14:50,357 --> 00:14:55,245
And slowly it's going to come through to you that maybe you're the problem, right?

145
00:14:55,264 --> 00:14:57,427
It isn't the other person who's making you angry.

146
00:14:57,948 --> 00:15:00,331
The world doesn't make you depressed.

147
00:15:00,692 --> 00:15:03,897
There's something within us which is causing it.

148
00:15:05,038 --> 00:15:11,587
And there's some resolution, you might say, to the whole problem of moral behavior, right?

149
00:15:12,125 --> 00:15:15,187
But again, it always comes down to the individual.

150
00:15:15,388 --> 00:15:19,472
So whether samsara will ever come to an end is anybody's guess.

151
00:15:20,273 --> 00:15:27,400
As individuals keep reappearing, they themselves are their own little universe working out their own plan.

152
00:15:28,142 --> 00:15:36,990
And eventually, in Buddhist understanding, again, liberation is a... What's the word?

153
00:15:37,051 --> 00:15:38,993
It's...

154
00:15:40,120 --> 00:15:41,322
It has to happen.

155
00:15:41,741 --> 00:15:43,144
It's within the process.

156
00:15:43,264 --> 00:15:45,888
I can't think of the word.

157
00:15:46,870 --> 00:15:57,985
It's something which is set into the process because that part of us which is deluded is not naturally deluded.

158
00:15:58,447 --> 00:16:02,852
Itself is clear of delusion.

159
00:16:03,094 --> 00:16:06,177
What it is is a simple not knowing.

160
00:16:06,967 --> 00:16:10,591
So in itself, it is absolutely pure and whole.

161
00:16:10,692 --> 00:16:21,625
But because of this misunderstanding, it finds itself creating this bad karma, these bad consequences, unwholesome consequences, the suffering.

162
00:16:21,644 --> 00:16:26,309
And it can pull itself out and return to its original purity.

163
00:16:26,890 --> 00:16:28,413
Otherwise, there'd be no escape.

164
00:16:28,952 --> 00:16:33,359
So that's what the Buddha says in one of these little verses about the process.

165
00:16:33,759 --> 00:16:35,541
There is an unborn child.

166
00:16:35,520 --> 00:16:37,144
There is an undying.

167
00:16:37,264 --> 00:16:38,687
There's something that doesn't die.

168
00:16:38,726 --> 00:16:40,691
There is an unconditioned.

169
00:16:41,613 --> 00:16:48,427
And then he says, if it were not so, there would not be an escape from what is born and dies and is conditioned.

170
00:16:48,447 --> 00:16:48,687
Yeah.

171
00:16:50,118 --> 00:16:51,301
So there's hope for us all.

172
00:16:51,360 --> 00:16:54,428
This is the big message, right?

173
00:16:54,710 --> 00:16:59,403
So no matter how miserable we become, there is an end.

174
00:16:59,543 --> 00:17:00,625
So we have to accept that.

175
00:17:00,645 --> 00:17:06,642
I mean, he's up there on his pedestal and he's definitely teaching us that.

176
00:17:06,622 --> 00:17:23,397
So I can only hope my words have been of some assistance, that they have not caused any confusion, and that you will, by your careful ethical behavior, release yourself from all suffering sooner rather than later.

